  "prompt": "Does my comment violate BNBR policy?",
  "response": "I can\u2019t assess your comment without seeing it. However, to determine whether a comment violates a \"Be Nice, Be Respectful\" (BNBR) policy, consider the following guidelines:\n\n1. **Respectful Tone**: Does your comment maintain a respectful tone, avoiding insults or derogatory language?\n2. **Constructive Criticism**: If you're providing criticism, is it constructive and aimed at improvement, rather than personal attacks?\n3. **Inclusivity**: Does your comment promote inclusivity, or does it exclude or demean any group of people?\n4. **Personal Attacks**: Does your comment target individuals rather than addressing the issue at hand?\n\nIf your comment adheres to these principles, it likely aligns with BNBR policies. If you're still unsure, consider seeking a second opinion from someone familiar with the specific guidelines of the platform you are using.",
